This a start-again-from-scratch .vim directory for me to use more easily across
my various machines. One more step towards independence of any particular
machine! It also allows for easy sharing of my vim config with others. To
fascilitate easy sharing (including with myself), you can find it on github
here (though you probably already knew this):

https://github.com/davclark/dotvim

To learn about the way I'm using pathogen and git submodules, check this link:

http://vimcasts.org/episodes/synchronizing-plugins-with-git-submodules-and-pathogen/
